### Feature Description

It would be great if we can have a `dir` signal.

Currently, to convert into a proper signal I have to do use `toSignal` in `ngOnInit`.

```ts
ngOnInit(): void {
  runInInjectionContext(this.injector, () => {
      this.direction = toSignal<Direction, Direction>(this.dir.change.pipe(map(() => this.dir.value)), { initialValue: this.dir.value });
  });
}
```

### Use Case

I want to be able to determine dir value as well as re-calculating stuff when dir changes, a combination of `dir.value` and `dir.changes`, a `dir()` signal inside `effect()` is needed.
